City of Los Angeles

************************************************************************


Record request #24-13091 has been closed. The closure reason supplied was:

Dear Requester:

&nbsp;

In regard to item 2, the Department has completed its review and is providing you with a record responsive to this portion of your request.

&nbsp;

Section 7922.000 provides an exemption where the public interest in non-disclosure clearly outweighs any interest in disclosure. The Department has a strong interest in maintaining the confidentiality of records that consist of or contain detailed operational information and analysis of potential threats. Disclosure of this information to the public has the potential to enable would-be perpetrators to discern areas of vulnerability and the intelligence assessments, evade security procedures, thereby endangering the operation of the Department and the safety of its officers and the public in the event of similar law enforcement initiatives.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

In regard to item 5, in accordance with the California Government Code, Sections 7923.600-7923.625, records of investigations conducted by, or investigatory files compiled by, any local police agency for law enforcement purposes are exempt from disclosure. To the extent that records were located, they are either investigatory records themselves or properly part of an investigative file. Therefore, we are denying your request.&nbsp;Should any records be located, they may be available in response to a subpoena or court order related to pending litigation.&nbsp;

&nbsp;

If you have any questions, please respond to this email.

&nbsp;

Respectfully,

&nbsp;

LAPD Public Records &amp; Subpoena Response Section, CPRA Unit








